'''Nimloth''' was an elf-maid of [[Doriath]], the daughter of [[Galathil]].<ref>{{UT|Galadriel}}, last paragraph before the section Concerning Galadriel and Celeborn, p. 233</ref><ref name="D">{{WJ|Years}}, stage 'D', p. 257</ref>

==History==
In {{FA|497}},<ref name="D" /> she wedded [[Dior]], King [[Thingol]]'s heir, and for a time lived with him by the [[Lanthir Lamath]], a waterfall at the base of the [[Blue Mountains]]. There she gave birth to [[Eluréd]] and [[Elurín]], her sons, and [[Elwing]] her only daughter.

After the murder of King Thingol, she returned to Doriath with her husband and became the queen of Doriath. Their reign was short-lived, however, as in [[Yule]] of {{FA|506}}<ref name="Nim">{{WJ|Years}}, stage 'D', manuscript 'D 2', p. 351</ref> the [[Sons of Fëanor]] [[Second Kinslaying|assaulted]] [[Menegroth]] and slew both her and Dior. Her sons, Eluréd and Elurín, were left in the forest to die by the servants of [[Celegorm]]. Elwing, however, escaped to the [[Mouths of Sirion|Havens of Sirion]].<ref>{{S|Doriath}}</ref>

==Etymology and names==
:''See: [[Nimloth (tree)#Etymology]]''
The name ''Nimloth'' is in [[Sindarin]]. It is also the same name as the name of the [[Nimloth (tree)|White Tree of Númenor]],<ref>{{UT|6e}}, fourth paragraph, p. 266</ref> which means "White Blossom".<ref>{{UT|Index}}, entry ''Nimloth (1)''</ref>

The earlier name '''''Lindis''''' is also in Sindarin. According to ''[[Eldamo]]'' it is composed of ''[[lind]]'' ("song") + ''[[dîs]]'' ("bride").<ref>{{webcite|author=[[Paul Strack]]|articleurl=http://eldamo.org/content/words/word-1378187557.html|articlename=S. ''Lindis'' f.|website=Eldamo|accessed=23 March 2022}}</ref>

The name '''''Elulin''''', according to ''Eldamo'', consists of the elements ''[[Elu]]'' (the Sindarin form of ''Elwë'') and ''lind'' ("song").<ref>{{webcite|author=[[Paul Strack]]|articleurl=http://eldamo.org/content/words/word-383406357.html|articlename=S. ''Elulin'' f.|website=Eldamo|accessed=23 March 2022}}</ref>

