==Other versions of the legendarium==
The first time Dior's wife was mentioned in the [[legendarium]], she was named '''''Lindis'''''.<ref name="D" /> An alternative name, '''''Elulin''''', was given to her at roughly the same time.<ref>{{WJ|Years}}, p. 350</ref>

On the other side of a table with the descendants of Elwë (Thingol), Nimloth is the daughter of Galadhon and the 'sister of Celeborn'. It looks as if the second thought of [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] was that Nimloth was the daughter of Galathil and the niece of Celeborn.<ref name="D" /> [[J.R.R. Tolkien|Tolkien's]] later writings offer an alternate ancestry for Celeborn.<ref>see ''[[Celeborn#Controversy|Celeborn]]''</ref>

